    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a 2002 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) featuring the 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six engine paired with a 6-speed manual transaxle. This M96 powerplant utilizes VarioCam Plus for optimized valve timing and lift, providing a linear power delivery up to its 7,300 RPM redline. Crucially, the IMS bearing has been retrofitted with a dual-row ceramic solution, and the Rear Main Seal (RMS) has been replaced to ensure long-term mechanical integrity. The chassis retains its factory torsional rigidity, supported by a MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension geometry that offers precise turn-in. While the exterior shows minor road-derived patina, the drivetrain is synchronized perfectly, with no signs of bore scoring or AOS failure. The braking system features four-piston monobloc calipers with cross-drilled rotors for superior heat dissipation during spirited driving.",
      "price": 32500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 20
    },
    {
